<h4><a name="en"></a><em>English</em></h4>

<h2>Welcome to the Mammouth Café</h2>

<p>In the spirit of <a target="_blank" href="http://tilde.club/">tilde.club</a>, here are a few, simple rules:</p>

<ul>
<li><em>Have fun. Be respectful. No drama.</em></li>
<li>There is NO GUILT here. NOR SHAME. Not knowing things is fine. Not finishing them is fine too.</li>
<li>We're all trying, and we're all in this together. :)</li>
<li>IMPORTANT NOTE: PLEASE DON'T HACK THE GIBSON.</li>
</ul>


<h3>Guidelines</h3>

<p>Aside from the general rules stated above, mammouth.cafe follows principles similar to <a target="_blank" href="https://mastodon.social/about/more">those of mastodon.social</a>, to wit:</p>

<ol>
<li>Absolutely no content allowed that would be illegal in Switzerland and/or France.</li>
<li>No discrimination, no racism, no xenophobia, no sexism, no incitement to hate or to violence of any kind.</li>
<li>We take a very dim view of stalking or harassment of other persons, here or elsewhere.<br>
Same goes for encouraging or inciting other people to take part in such activities.</li>
<li>There are CW (Content Warning) and NSFW (Not Safe For Work) options: use them accordingly when you post.</li>
<li>No hard or child/minor pornography of any kind, and keep material of an erotic nature behind CW and/or NSFW filters.</li>
<li>No gore or extremely graphic violence.</li>
<li>No spam, no ads, no affiliate links or excessive promotion.<br>
Of course, you are still welcome to announce your latest comic, self-published novella or upcoming local amateur theatre stage play to our community.</li>
<li>We discourage any sort of corporate accounts: we prefer to keep it personal.<br>
On the other hand, educational institutions, associations and other non-profit organisations (such as e.g. amateur dramatics groups) are warmly welcome.</li>
<li>No fake accounts, even celebrity joke accounts.</li>
<li>We discourage bots, unless they're cute or friendly.</li>
<li>Robots that bang on the server will get bitcanned.</li>
<li>Replicants are like any other machine: they’re either a benefit or a hazard. If they’re a benefit, it’s not our problem.</li>
<li>No zombies allowed under any circumstance.</li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.gnuterrypratchett.com/">GNU Terry Pratchett</a>.</li>
</ol>

<p>Final interpretation and implementation of these rules, guidelines and of general good netiquette, as well as all decisions that may result in account suspension and/or revocation of access, will be up to the administration of mammouth.cafe.</p>


<h3>Support</h3>

<p>Support is available: ping <em>@support@mammouth.cafe</em>.</p>

<p>For status updates, planned downtimes and so on, you can follow <em>@status@mammouth.cafe</em>.</p>
    
<p>Please remember: this is essentially a one-man show for now, so do not expect an answer within the hour. If it's urgent, try asking the community: someone may be able to lend you a hand.</p>

<p>We'll try not to mess things up, but we probably will at some point. If you feel that what you post here is vital to you, do make a backup somewhere else (atom feeds are available for every account) or, even better, give some of your time and knowledge to help us out with this thing.</p>


<h3>Handling abuse and harassment</h3>

<p>If you are being abused or harassed, please report the user using the "…" button and then "Report."</p>

<p>If you engage in abusing or harassing behavior, the administration may take any action we deem appropriate, such as an account suspension or revocation of access.</p>

<p>Abuse is anything we say it is. Too bad if you disagree.</p>


<h3>Blocked instances</h3>

<p>We do <a target="_blank" href="https://gitlab.com/mammouthcafe/mamont-documentation/blob/master/blocked-instances.md">block some Mastodon instances</a> where a sizeable part of their community infringes our rules and/or guidelines with their behaviour. We do not usually comment on individual accounts muting, suspension or removal.</p>


<h3>Privacy and security</h3>

<p>We value your privacy. We are here to have fun, not to make any money by throwing ads down your throat or monetizing the shit out of your online activities. No ads or trackers are installed on this instance.</p>

<p>Please understand however that mammouth.cafe's administrators have potentially access to your data, including your direct messages. The backend is also not encrypted. If this is not all right with you, this might not be the instance you're looking for.</p>

<p>Finally, a word of advice: consider this a public space. Whatever you publish here is public and can (and probably will) be read by someone else or potentially be archived by the <a target="_blank" href="https://archive.org">Internet Archive</a> and/or other similar insititutions.</p>
    
<p>We'll try to keep things reasonably safe, but if you need to keep your sources confidential or you are involved in activities that may put yourself or others in jeopardy in your country or elsewhere, please take into account the fact that we won't be able to offer you the necessary confidentiality and/or security here.</p>

<p>Also, for truly private data sent between two people, Mastodon offers no end-to-end encryption. Use a dedicated E2E application with good reputation, like e.g. Signal, for the communications you really want to keep private.</p>

<p>And remember to always practice safe hex.</p>


<h3>About this instance</h3>

<p>This instance is run by <a target="_blank" href="https://www.mammouth.ch">Atelier Mammouth</a> in a TARDIS somewhere/time in a big ball of wibbly-wobbly timey-wimey... stuff.</p>

<p>For the time being, costs for running this server are pretty reasonable and the admin can afford them. If you wish to support this thing, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.patreon.com/user/posts?u=619786">give something to Eugen Rochko, aka @Gargron</a> (Mastodon's dad) instead, please. Thank you so much!</p>


<p><em>And remember: this is FREE software and...</em></p>

